      { q: 'Define the natural rate of unemployment.', marks: 2, tier: 'green', modelAnswer: 'The natural rate of unemployment is the level of unemployment that exists when the labour market is in equilibrium. It consists of frictional and structural unemployment and exists even when the economy is at full employment (no cyclical unemployment).' },
      { q: 'State three components of the current account of the balance of payments.', marks: 3, tier: 'green', modelAnswer: 'Three components: (1) Trade in goods - exports and imports of physical products. (2) Trade in services - exports and imports of services such as financial services, tourism, and insurance. (3) Primary income - investment income from overseas assets and payments to foreign owners of domestic assets.' }
